wikipedia_page.main: Daniel King (18 January 1784 in Funtington, Sussex – 26 June 1836 in Chichester, Sussex) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) who was active in the 1810s. He is recorded in one match in 1814, totalling 14 runs with a highest score of 8.
